                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13419353" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Fri, 20 Jul 2012 17:06:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm..almost looks like i thought this mostly because of a ui bug - i think perhaps its showing green for a moment when it should not. When i try and check the same thing through the zk tree, it looks right.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I did tighten things so that the leader for sure sees a down state before the replica registers its live node though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13419686" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Fri, 20 Jul 2012 23:33:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I committed a bit to perhaps toughen this - but I&apos;m not sure what is going on with the UI yet - though I&apos;ve tried a bit of debugging. I&apos;ve got to check out the zk servlet next - have not looked at that before.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13429803" author="rcmuir" created="Tue, 7 Aug 2012 03:43:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;rmuir20120906-bulk-40-change&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13452188" author="rcmuir" created="Mon, 10 Sep 2012 17:41:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;moving all 4.0 issues not touched in a month to 4.1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13509324" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Mon, 3 Dec 2012 23:28:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;note: i still see this &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13528539" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Tue, 11 Dec 2012 00:59:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So I think it&apos;s the result of a node getting the updated live nodes and having stale cluster state...we should address it somehow.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13543030" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Thu, 3 Jan 2013 16:17:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To elaborate - we get the live nodes and cluster state independently - and live nodes should be much faster to get.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13574811" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Fri, 8 Feb 2013 20:53:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve gotten to the bottom of this - patch attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
